{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/update-patch-aks","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Recently I came across two situations where I had to make changes to some components in an AKS cluster with minimum impact. I didn't want to be applying the full <code class=\"language-text\">yaml</code> files again since I was not too familiar with this particular set up.</p>\n<h2 id=\"updating-an-image\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#updating-an-image\" aria-label=\"updating an image permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Updating an image</h2>\n<p>The first change I had to make was a replace of a docker image that one of the services was using. For that I updated the AKS deployment.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Updates the Image</span>\nkubectl <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">set</span> image deployment/iothub-manager iothub-manager-pod<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>goncalvesj/iothub-manager-dotnet:01 --record\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Checks status</span>\nkubectl rollout status deployment/iothub-manager\n<span class=\"token comment\"># If something goes wrong use this to rollback the update</span>\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/iothub-manager</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"updating-an-ingress\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#updating-an-ingress\" aria-label=\"updating an ingress permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Updating an Ingress</h2>\n<p>The second change was to expose another service in an ingress controller, for that I used a combination of <code class=\"language-text\">JSON</code> and the <code class=\"language-text\">kubectl</code> patch command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\"># JSON to add one extra path and service.\n# This will append the extra path at the end of the ingress controller paths section.\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"op\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"add\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"path\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"/spec/rules/0/http/paths/-\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"value\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"path\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"/storageadapter\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"backend\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token property\">\"serviceName\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"storage-adapter-svc\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token property\">\"servicePort\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">9022</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Executes the patch</span>\nkubectl patch ingress remotemonitoring --type json -p <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">cat</span> patch.json<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>Hope this helped!</strong></p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Recently I came across two situations where I had to make changes to some components in an AKS cluster with minimum impact. I didn't want toâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Updating and Patching AKS","cover":"https://unsplash.it/400/300/?random?BigTest","date":"2020-04-15T00:00:00.000Z","categories":["Azure","AKS"],"tags":["AKS"]},"fields":{"slug":"/update-patch-aks","date":"April 14, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/update-patch-aks","nexttitle":"Deploying a Gatsby blog in GitHub pages","nextslug":"/deploy-gatsby-github-pages","prevtitle":"Getting Started with Terraform","prevslug":"/getting-started-terraform"}}}